- You should use sha1.c, sha1.h, md5.c and md5.h in your project.
- We supplied two test programs: md5test.c and sha1test.c. Both receive 
input strings as arguments, compute the hash values and print them.
- Just run
gcc md5.c md5test.c -o md5test
md5test name1 name2 david barak

gcc sha1.c sha1test.c -o sha1test
sha1test name1 name2 david barak

-----------------------------------------------
SHA1 code is based on the source code from-
http://www.packetizer.com/security/sha1/
(the c package).

Check Wikipedia - 
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHA_hash_functions
and the RFC -
http://www.apps.ietf.org/rfc/rfc3174.html
for more details.

-----------------------------------------------
MD5 code is based on the source code from-
http://people.csail.mit.edu/rivest/Md5.c

Check Wikipedia-
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MD5
and the RFC-
http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc1321
for more details.


